section.t:
Additionally, the following rules are included from : URI and
        URI-Reference; from : type-name and subtype-name; from : MediaDesc; from : Language-Tag;
        and from , ext-value and parmname.

When extension relation types are compared, they MUST be compared as strings (after converting to URIs
			if serialised in a different format, such as a Curie ) in a case-insensitive fashion,
			 character-by-character. Because of this, all-lowercase URIs SHOULD be used for extension relations.

